# Bingo (Remote & Non-Remote) - Money Laundering and Terrorist Financing Risk Assessment 2023

**Overall Risk Rating:** High (Remote) / Medium (Non-Remote)

## Summary

Bingo operations present different risk levels depending on delivery method. Remote bingo is rated as high risk due to challenges with customer verification, multiple account accessibility, and payment method vulnerabilities. Non-remote (land-based) bingo halls are rated as medium risk, with physical customer presence and lower transaction limits providing some mitigation.

---

## Remote Bingo - Inherent Risks

### Operator Control Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| Operators failing to comply with prevention of money laundering and terrorist financing legislation and guidance | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| Operators staking and winning directly and indirectly on their own products | Low (1) | Medium (2) | Low (2) | No change |
| Poor source of funds checks | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| Inadequate or lack of 'know your customer' (KYC) checks | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| Third party business relationships and business investors | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |

### Licensing and Integrity Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| Gambling operations run by organised criminals to launder criminally derived funds | Low (1) | High (3) | Medium (3) | No change |

### Customer Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| Customer not physically present for identification | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| False or stolen documentation used to bypass controls to launder criminally derived funds | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | No change |
| Accessibility to multiple remote accounts | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | Decrease in likelihood |
| Customers on the sanction list | Low (1) | High (3) | Medium (3) | New risk rating |
| Use of third parties or agents to obscure the source or ownership of money gambled by customers and their identities | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |
| 'Smurfing' | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |

### Means of Payment Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| Cryptoasset transactions | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |
| Pre-paid cards | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | Decrease in likelihood |
| Multiple methods of payment | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk |
| E-wallets | Medium (2) | Medium (2) | Medium (4) | No change |

